### Quick Test - TextToSqlAgent API
### For development only - requires disabling [Authorize] attribute temporarily
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5251

###############################################################################
# QUICK TESTS (No Auth - Development Only)
###############################################################################

### 1. Health Check (Always works - has [AllowAnonymous])
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/health

### 2. Dev Query - No Auth Required (Development Only!)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/dev/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Show me all customers"
}

### 3. Dev Query - Top 10 Customers (No Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/dev/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Show me top 10 customers by revenue"
}

### 4. Dev Query - Complex Query (No Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/dev/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Show me customers who have placed orders with total amount greater than 1000"
}

###############################################################################
# AUTHENTICATION FLOW (Use this for production testing)
###############################################################################

### 5. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@test.com",
  "password": "Dev123!",
  "fullName": "Dev User"
}

### 6. Login and Get Token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@test.com",
  "password": "Dev123!"
}

###############################################################################
# AGENT TESTS (With Auth)
###############################################################################

### 7. Check Agent Mode
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/mode
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

### 8. Simple Query (With Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/query
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "question": "Show me all customers"
}

### 9. Top 10 Customers by Revenue (With Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/query
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "question": "Show me top 10 customers by revenue"
}

### 10. Get Schema (With Auth)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/agent/schema
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

###############################################################################
# INSTRUCTIONS
###############################################################################

# HOW TO USE FOR QUICK TESTING (No Auth):
# 
# 1. Start the API: dotnet run --project TextToSqlAgent.API
# 
# 2. Run development endpoints (no auth needed):
#    - Request #1: Health Check
#    - Request #2-4: Dev Query endpoints (no authentication required!)
#
# ⚠️  WARNING: /api/agent/dev/query is for DEVELOPMENT ONLY!
#     Remove or secure this endpoint before deploying to production!
#
# HOW TO USE WITH AUTHENTICATION (Production):
# 
# 1. Start the API: dotnet run --project TextToSqlAgent.API
# 
# 2. Run requests in order:
#    - Request #5: Register User (first time only)
#    - Request #6: Login (get JWT token)
#    - Request #7-10: Use the token from login
#
# 3. The token is automatically captured from login response
#    and used in subsequent requests via {{login.response.body.token}}
#
# 4. If you get 401 Unauthorized:
#    - Re-run the Login request (#6) to get a fresh token
#    - Tokens expire after 3 hours
#
# ENDPOINTS WITHOUT AUTH:
# - GET /api/agent/health (always available)
# - POST /api/agent/dev/query (development only!)
#
# ENDPOINTS WITH AUTH:
# - GET /api/agent/mode
# - POST /api/agent/query
# - GET /api/agent/schema
# - POST /api/agent/schema/refresh
#
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
# Before deploying to production, you should:
# 1. Remove the /api/agent/dev/query endpoint
# 2. Or add environment check to disable it in production
# 3. Ensure all sensitive endpoints require authentication
